						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine, of the Vṛiddhagirīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 13: 984 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records the gift of 1/4 <hi rend="italic">chey (vēli)</hi> of land made tax-free for providing food offerings to the sun god in Tirumudukuṉṟam by the <hi rend="italic">ūrār</hi> of Neṟkuppai. This was reclaimed through the efforts of one Kavidikkuḍi Kūttan Kulamāni of Neṟkuppai.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX. No. 325.</p>						

